election_record.label: New Jersey 1808 U.S. House of Representatives

sub_unit.name: Essex
sub_unit.note: Poulson's American Daily Advertiser (Philadelphia, PA) November 17, 1808 and The Centinel of Freedom (Newark, NJ) November 22, 1808 both give 588 votes for W. Cox, but doing the addition, with the township totals as listed in the New-Jersey Telescope (Newark, NJ) November 8, 1808, you get the above total.
The New-Jersey Telescope (Newark, NJ) lists total of 3220 for J. Hufty, but doing the addition, with the township figures, results in above total.

sub_unit.name: Greenwich
sub_unit.note: Samuel W. Harrison received 1 vote as Samuel Harrison.

sub_unit.name: Salem
sub_unit.note: On the Original Election Returns from Salem County, the 32 votes listed for John Neilson in the town of Elsinborough have been scratched out and his county wide total listed as 577.

sub_unit.note: Samuel W. Harrison received 1 vote as Samuel Harrison.
